 the ADM tensor, and Bondi energy identities and inequalities.The book is self-contained, providing complete proofs and precise statements, which develop a refined theory for solutions of quasilinear Klein-Gordon and wave equations, including novel linear and bilinear estimates. Only mild decay assumptions are made on the scalar field and the initial metric is allowed to have nonisotropic decay consistent with the positive mass theorem. The framework incorporates analysis both in physical and Fourier space, and is compatible with previous results on other physical models such as water waves and plasma physics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGeneral relativity (Physics) 0aGeneral relativity (Physics). 0aKlein-Gordon equation. 0aMathematical physics. 0aQuantum field theory. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Mathematical & Computational.2bisacsh  aAddition.  aAlgebraic structure.  aAntiderivative.  aApproximation.  aAsymptote.  aAsymptotic analysis.  aBending.  aBig O notation.  aBootstrapping (statistics).  aCalculation.  aCauchy distribution.  aCoefficient.  aCombination.  aCompact space.  aComplex number.  aComputation.  aConserved quantity.  aCoordinate system.  aCoordinate-free.  aCovariant derivative.  aDerivative.  aDifferential operator.  aDispersion relation.  aEinstein field equations.  aEnergy functional.  aEquation.  aEstimation.  aExponential growth.  aFoliation.  aFourier analysis.  aFourier transform.  aFunction (mathematics).  aFunction space.  aGeneral relativity.  aGeodesic.  aGeodesics in general relativity.  aGeographic coordinate system.  aGeometry.  aGlobal analysis.  aGlobality.  aHigh frequency.  aHyperboloid.  aHypersurface.  aHypothesis.  aImplementation.  aIngredient.  aIntegration by parts.  aInterpol